race.comment: ILGIRO DELMONDO (5) was quickly back on track beaten 1.3L over 1850m at Toodyay. Three back she missed a whisker over 2200m at Belmont and that's good form. Maps well and is capable of running a bold race. LUTZ (4) was good when lipped out at last time at Carnarvon over 2000m. Has a 3kg claimer up today and is among the winning chances. REGINALD (1) scored a 0.6L at Newman two starts back. Was outgraded following at Belmont Park and forget. Don't underestimate him back on dirt. DIVINE MERCY (3) started at $7 last time beaten 4L at Carnarvon in the LUTZ race. Missed a lip there prior and a 3kg claimer goes back on. Has to be considered. THE ROOSTER (7) had strong lead-up form into the latest but was plain. On a quick backup and keep onside.
